cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.SI, cs.NI, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the use of spatially coupled interleaving to improve the performance of iterative multiuser detection and decoding, which is a topic related to information theory. 
2. cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) - The paper deals with multiuser detection and decoding in a fading MIMO system, which is a topic related to communications and networking. 
3. cs.SI (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a sliding window MUDD to circumvent an increase of the decoding latency due to SC interleaving, which is a topic related to systems and control. 
4. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the use of spatially coupled interleaving to improve the performance of iterative multiuser detection and decoding, which is a topic related to networking and internet architecture. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes the use of linear minimum mean-squared error (LMMSE) demodulator to reduce the complexity and to avoid error propagation, which is a topic related to data structures and algorithms.
